The IP-XACT file is used to configure the pck600_clk_ctrl. The configuration options are:

NUM_Q_CHL              : Configures the number of the device Q-Channel interfaces. Default value is 1. Range is 1 to 8. This maps to the NUM_Q_CHL verilog parameter.

NUM_QACTIVE_ONLY       : Configures the number of the QACTIVE only device Q-Channel interfaces. Default value is 1. Range is 0 to 32. This maps to the NUM_QACTIVE_ONLY verilog parameter.

HC_Q_CH_SYNC           : Includes or excludes synchronizers on HC Q-Channels. Default value is 1. Possible values are {0,1}. This maps to the HC_Q_CH_SYNC verilog parameter.

PWR_Q_CH_SYNC          : Includes or excludes synchronizers on PWR Q-Channels. Default value is 1. Possible values are {0,1}. This maps to the HC_Q_CH_SYNC verilog parameter.

CLK_Q_CH_SYNC          : Includes or excludes synchronizers on CLK Q-Channels. Default value is 1. Possible values are {0,1}. This maps to the HC_Q_CH_SYNC verilog parameter.

CLK_QACTIVE_SYNC       : Includes or excludes synchronizers on CLK Qactive. Default value is 1. Possible values are {0,1}. This maps to the CLK_QACTIVE_SYNC verilog parameter.

ACTIVE_DENY_EN         : Configures to support or not the use of CLK_QACTIVE as denies for quiescence request. Default value is 1. Possible values are {0,1}. This maps to the ACTIVE_DENY_EN verilog parameter.
